<item>
            <title>[AVRO-1259] improve Trevni encoding of sparse fields</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1259</link>
                <project id="12310911" key="AVRO">Apache Avro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If in most records a field is null, Trevni writes a null byte (zero length) for that record in that column.  This might be optimized by instead using a run-length encoding for lengths.  The length is signed, so negative lengths might be used to indicate the number of zero-lengths before the next non-zero value.  This could thus be back-compatible.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12633106">AVRO-1259</key>
            <summary>improve Trevni encoding of sparse fields</summary>
                <type id="4" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21140&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Improvement</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg">Major</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
                                    <resolution id="1">Fixed</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="cutting">Doug Cutting</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="cutting">Doug Cutting</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Wed, 20 Feb 2013 00:42:57 +0000</created>
                <updated>Tue, 20 Aug 2013 17:46:04 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Wed, 27 Mar 2013 23:42:50 +0000</resolved>
                                                    <fixVersion>1.7.5</fixVersion>
                                    <component>trevni</component>
                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>2</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13591121" author="cutting" created="Sat, 2 Mar 2013 00:00:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch that implements this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;No new tests are required, since TestShredder already writes and reads various sequences of zero lengths.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13591135" author="cutting" created="Sat, 2 Mar 2013 00:16:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For a union like &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;quot;null&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;int&amp;quot;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, Trevni writes two columns, one for null values and one for the ints.  Each is written as a sequence of &amp;lt;length&amp;gt;&amp;lt;value&amp;gt; pairs, where the length is always either zero or one.  With this optimization, if most values are null, then the int column will be compactly written as &amp;lt;rowsToSkip&amp;gt;&amp;lt;intValue&amp;gt;&amp;lt;rowsToSkip&amp;gt;&amp;lt;intValue&amp;gt;..., but the null column will still be written as &amp;lt;isNull&amp;gt;&amp;lt;isNull&amp;gt;...  (Since the nulls themselves have no size, the column just records which rows have a null value for the union and which do not.)  This could be improved if we also run-length encoded ones.  We might, e.g., even negative values for zero runs and odd negative values for one runs.  Then a the null column for a sparse value would look like &amp;lt;nullCount&amp;gt;&amp;lt;nullCount&amp;gt;...  Similarly, if a &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;quot;null&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;int&amp;quot;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; nearly always has a non-null value then the null column would look like &amp;lt;rowsToSkip&amp;gt;&amp;lt;rowsToSkip&amp;gt;... while the int column would have &amp;lt;valueCount&amp;gt;&amp;lt;int&amp;gt;&amp;lt;int&amp;gt;...  In general, optimizing zeros and ones both would greatly improve the representations of unions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13591139" author="cutting" created="Sat, 2 Mar 2013 00:19:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that if you project a &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;quot;null&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;int&amp;quot;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; union down to simply &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;quot;int&amp;quot;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; then Trevni only processes the int column and sets the value of the field to null for rows where it has a non-int value.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13601684" author="cutting" created="Wed, 13 Mar 2013 21:36:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch that run-length encodes both zero and one lengths.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13602625" author="cutting" created="Thu, 14 Mar 2013 19:43:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Update version number in file &amp;amp; spec.  This is a back-compatible change, but not forward compatible.  Perhaps it should slip to 1.8.0?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13615892" author="cutting" created="Wed, 27 Mar 2013 23:42:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I committed this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13616956" author="hudson" created="Fri, 29 Mar 2013 01:30:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in AvroJava #360 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/AvroJava/360/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/AvroJava/360/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1259&quot; title=&quot;improve Trevni encoding of sparse fields&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AVRO-1259&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AVRO-1259&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Java: Improve Trevni&apos;s encoding of sparse columns. (Revision 1461896)&lt;/p&gt;

