                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13581855" author="martinkl" created="Wed, 20 Feb 2013 01:40:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch attached.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13583368" author="cutting" created="Thu, 21 Feb 2013 17:41:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Martin, this change looks like it might not be back-compatible.  Existing Ruby applications that use, e.g., Schema::PRIMITIVE_TYPES won&apos;t work as before.  So probably we should include this in 1.8.0 rather than 1.7.4?  (Avro permits incompatible API changes in point releases.  Major releases imply an incompatible change to data formats.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13584942" author="martinkl" created="Sat, 23 Feb 2013 01:46:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Doug, when do you expect 1.8.0 to happen? In general I&apos;d be ok with delaying it, but since the patch touches so many lines of code, it&apos;s likely to conflict with other changes that are made (i.e. the longer we wait, the greater the chance that it won&apos;t apply any more). So if 1.8.0 is still a while away, I can try harder to make it backwards-compatible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13584946" author="martinkl" created="Sat, 23 Feb 2013 01:55:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;(Of course I mean delaying applying this patch until 1.8.0, not delaying a release. Sorry for the ambiguity.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13585190" author="martinkl" created="Sat, 23 Feb 2013 18:51:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have attached an updated patch (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1260&quot; title=&quot;Ruby: Performance improvements for parsing&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AVRO-1260&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AVRO-1260&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;-2.patch) that maintains full backwards compatibility: constants are left unchanged, and all methods continue to accept the same arguments and return the same result as before.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Missed the boat for 1.7.4, but here you go anyway &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13590833" author="cutting" created="Fri, 1 Mar 2013 19:03:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks great!  I tested the back compatibility by applying the patch then reverting the changes to random_data.rb and io.rb.  Tests still passed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I committed this.  Thanks, Martin!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
